# Website message-template form UX

Authoritative flow: `docs/platforms/website/flow-customer-message-templates.md` §6.

## Locked

- Placeholder **chip labels** are human-readable i18n strings — never show `{{token}}` on the chip. Tokens appear only inside the text field value after insert.
- Insert chips live in `FormInputWrapper.headerArea` **above** the input — not in `actionArea` beside the title.
- `ADWHATS_PRO` variables table: human labels + editable **variable number** (slot). Do not label UI “Meta slot”.
- `ADWHATS_PRO` requires `meta_template_id` on the form (write-required on backend).
- Channel picker `messageChannels`: `searchable: false`; always filter `status: ACTIVE` + matching `type`; forward `selected` into `CustomerMessageChannelCard`.
- Kind content unused on other types: backend Joi `.strip()` — do not require frontend to clear unused keys as the primary contract.

## Forbidden

- Reverting chip copy to raw `{{memberName}}`-style labels.
- Putting insert tools beside the field title instead of above the field.
- Showing raw placeholder tokens in the Pro variables table.
- Channel picker without `ACTIVE` (unless product explicitly changes picker policy).
